args:
My conducting today was simply awful.
I did not make good use of each
individual's talent, and the collective
result was nothing short of a mess.
Can't believe that audience member\nthought they could go at the boss like that.
My apologies. You are Fritz from the\ncircus troupe, are you not?
That's me. And you're that conductor guy\nnamed Vixel, yeah?
Seems like I heard you grumbling\njust now.
I could say the same of you. Perhaps\nwe're more alike than I suspected.
And maybe you ain't the goody\ntwo-shoes I took you for at first.
Well, it seems we both have some\nissues bubbling under the surface.\nHow very surprising.
You are an entertainer; a man who\nlives always in the public eye.
It's difficult for such a man to keep\nskeletons in his closet.
And you're a conductor, which just makes\nyou a different kind of entertainer.
One needs more than surface knowledge to\nplay first-rate music. There are certain...\nsacrifices that must be made.
I hear that. Hell, I polished my dagger-\nthrowing skills on living targets.
It seems everyone has a story.
And a few they'd rather keep hidden.
So what was your deal, music man?\nDid you smash out church windows with\niron pipes and hijack carriages like I did?
No—but I did used to walk around looking\nfor any excuse to fight. Even the smallest\nof stray glances was enough for me.
Ha ha! I used to punch out any fool\nwho even looked at me cross-eyed!\nIn fact... Huh?
I'm sorry! I didn't mean to look at you!\nPlease don't beat me with a pipe!
Who the—how long have you been\nstanding there?!
I just wanted your autograph, mister...
And I wanted to give a gift to Vixel,\nbut now I fear I've stumbled into a\nconversation most sordid and dire!
Uhhh... Give us one tick here.
We'll need to talk our way out of this.\nYou begin, and I will make sure that\nmy story matches yours to a T.
...All right, you two. It's time to witness\nthe true power of the circus.

Ladieeeees and geeeeentlemen!
Prepare for a magical, mystical,
MARVELOUS circus unlike anything
you've ever seen before!
Sweet Ilia! You're going to beat us about\nthe head and shoulders with pipes!
Nobody's beatin' nobody with a pipe!\n...We're gonna show you a secret.
Er, yes. For you see, you have stumbled\nupon our secret plan to fuse the world of\nthe circus with the world of music!
Right! And it turns out one of our ideas\ninvolves using daggers to smash stained\nglass into little bits.
That's what we were discussing when you\ncame up behind us. Apologies if we\nsomehow gave the wrong impression.
Ah, but mere words are not enough.\nLet us show you a working version\nof our act to make it up to you!
I will sing, while he throws daggers\nat targets in time to the music.
Naturally, he will not miss a single one.\n...Er, right?
Okay, now I TOTALLY need your autograph!
I can't believe I'm hearing Vixel sing in\nperson... My heart feels like it's going\nto thump right out of my chest! *siiigh*
We're glad you enjoyed our show.\nDo come again!
It's been a long time since I've sung in\nfront of a live audience, and I would\nprefer to put the experience behind me.
Regardless, though we managed to\nworm our way out of trouble this time,\nwe should be more careful in the future.
Our work may be different, but we both\nchose to live in the public eye.
We cannot destroy the dreams they\nexpect us to create.
Yeah, nobody wants to know the sordid\ndetails of a dagger-thrower's past.
Besides, I worked this hard so I could\nleave those bloody alleys behind me.\nI can't go slipping back now.
I owe it to my fans AND myself.
Well said indeed. Let us continue to strive\nfor excellence in all that we do!
And on that note, I must cease lamenting\nmy failures and return to my studies.
Sounds like a plan to me.
...Oh, but let's make sure to meet up in\nsecret every now and then, yeah?
We can talk about our pasts, or maybe\nthis new act we're putting together.
Hmm. Actually, that might be something\nof a lark, now that I think about it.
And it could also be a truly dazzling show!
